reviews.text:
Over 30 years, and I barely remember it.  I passed by this place often.  It finally piqued my interest because there's a billboard for it leaving Spring Grove, headed toward 30, on 116.

Good pizza as far as strip mall pizzas go.  Not as much grease as other places.  Still had to soak it up with napkins.

Inside was decent.  I liked the table clothes, although they were beat up.  The place could use an upgrade.  It was pretty clean thoggh.  But I'm sure it pulls in some good business.  While I was there, they had a few people coming in for takeout.

I liked the simple, go up to the counter and order.  No where did I see a sign asking for tip.  I paid with a card and had no annoying screen asking me to pay a tip. If you have tip fatigue, this place is great!

1st visit went well , although they were busy and our order was confused with another customer.
Classic pizza shop eats and flavors.
2nd visit left me wondering... ordered pizza and wings ...but our pizza just sat as a Togo even tho we were dining in..
They got some work to do with staff, I think

Stopped in to check out a cheese pizza and was not disappointed. Right of the bat i could tell the cheese was the kind that I like. The sauce was realllly good too.  The overall flavor reminds me of my favorite local pizza place

My two year old is literally in love with Shakey Jakes pizza!!! She ate 4 slices from a large pizza to herself. The pizza & wings are so good although I wish the wings came in a bigger quantity than 12 max but otherwise I love their food. Customer service & delivery is very good. 10/10 would totally recommend!

Visiting York from out of town. I had an inch to eat some Stromboli like one does in Pennsylvania. We were lucky enough Shakey Jakes was open until 11. My team and I visited and most of us ordered a Boli. We were told a small would feed one person. So I ordered a large.
Holy Stromboli, this thing was huge. I only got through half but I brought it home so I can enjoy it for the next two days. It was so good I felt like it was sent from heaven above. This was EASILY the best food I have ever eaten in Pennsylvania. I can't recommend Shakey Jakes enough. Can't wait to go there again in 3 days when I finally finish my large Boli.

customerMoodAnalysis.sentimentSummary: Customers are genuinely thrilled with their experience. With an average 4.8/5 rating across 5 recent reviews, your restaurant consistently exceeds expectations.

strengthsPerceived: Customers appreciate the authentic and satisfying flavors of the pizza and Stromboli, which remind them of their favorite local places. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
The restaurant's no-tip policy and straightforward ordering process are highly valued by customers experiencing tip fatigue. - SEO services can leverage this for better visibility
The large portion sizes, especially the Stromboli, are a hit with customers who enjoy leftovers and value for money. - review management can highlight this positive aspect
improvementOpportunities: Order confusion and service issues - review management can address this concern
Long wait times and order mishandling - Boostly marketing services can improve this
